21 WHEREAS, Jacob Seth Lofland was born on July 30, 1996, in Briggsville,
22 Arkansas, to Debra and Billy Lofland, and is an actor widely known for his
23 portrayal of "Neckbone", which was his first acting role, in the famed
24 Arkansas-made film "Mud"; and
25
26 WHEREAS, Lofland obtained the acting role in "Mud" during a time when
27 his mother was working with a community group focused on bringing employment
28 opportunities to Fourche Valley in Yell County, and she was excited to see a
29 newspaper article noting that a Hollywood movie was going to be filming in
30 east Arkansas; and
31
32 WHEREAS, Lofland and his mother realized that Lofland perfectly fit the
33 description of the boy the director of "Mud", Jeff Nichols, was seeking to
34 cast as "Neckbone" because he was a teenaged Arkansas boy who could operate a
35 boat and ride a motorcycle; and
